rComments: One of the best profs I've ever had. I didn't do super well in the course, but that was on me; extremely patient and caring prof; knows his stuff too!
He is a very caring instructor and explains all concepts very thoroughly.

He is hands down the best prof i've ever had at UofT. Not only is he brilliant but he takes such care in ensuring his students understand the content , it's refreshing. His lectures are clear and he answers everyone's questions. It's the ONLY course i have not missed one single lecture in. Why? Because his teaching is that good. strongly recommend.

A great professor. Best math prof i had in university. He cares about what his students are learning,and he is always accessible outside class for office hours. Would definitely take a math course he is teaching.

He truly cares about making sure all his students understand the concepts, and it comes across during his lectures. Even during exams, he goes the extra mile to make sure students have no doubts about what they need to do. He's also always available for appointments for students who need extra help. One of the best profs at UofT!
